'''ᱠᱟᱨᱛᱤᱠ ᱛᱤᱣᱟᱨᱤ''' (ᱡᱟᱱᱟᱢ ᱒᱒ ᱱᱚᱣᱟᱢᱵᱚᱨ ᱑᱙᱙᱐<!-- DO NOT CHANGE! This has been verified by a high-quality reliable source-->), ᱫᱚ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱚ ᱴᱷᱮᱱ '''ᱠᱟᱨᱛᱤᱠ ᱟᱨᱭᱟᱱ''' ᱢᱮᱱᱛᱮ ᱵᱟᱰᱟᱭ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱢᱤᱫ ᱵᱚᱞᱤᱣᱩᱰ ᱟᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱵᱟᱭᱳᱴᱮᱠᱱᱳᱞᱳᱡᱤ(biotechnology) ᱨᱮ ᱤᱝᱡᱤᱱᱤᱭᱚᱨᱤᱝ ᱯᱟᱲᱦᱟᱜ ᱚᱠᱛᱚ ᱨᱮ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱢᱚᱰᱮᱞᱤᱝ ᱮᱦᱚᱵ ᱞᱮᱫᱟᱭ ᱟᱨ ᱟᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱵᱮᱱᱟᱜ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱡᱚᱥ ᱫᱚᱦᱚ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱯᱮ ᱥᱮᱨᱢᱟ ᱚᱱᱟ ᱫᱷᱟ.ᱲ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱷᱟᱴᱟᱣ ᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱒᱐᱑᱑ ᱥᱟ.ᱦᱤᱛ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟᱨᱛᱤᱠ, ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ''[[ᱯᱭᱟᱨ ᱠᱟ ᱯᱚᱧᱪᱱᱟᱢᱟ]]'' ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱧᱟᱢ ᱠᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱱᱚᱶᱟ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱫᱚ [[ᱞᱚᱵᱷ ᱨᱚᱱᱡᱚᱱ]]-ᱮ ᱰᱤᱨᱮᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱞᱮᱰᱤ ᱟᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ [[ᱱᱩᱥᱨᱚᱛ ᱵᱷᱚᱨᱩᱪᱟ]] ᱢᱮᱱᱟᱭᱟ ᱾

ᱠᱟᱨᱛᱤᱠ ''[[ᱟᱠᱟᱥ ᱵᱟᱬᱤ]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱓) ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱠᱟᱧᱪᱤ: ᱫᱤ ᱚᱱᱵᱽᱨᱮᱠᱮᱵᱚᱞ]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱔) ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱠᱮᱭᱟ ᱛᱚᱵᱮ ᱱᱚᱶᱟ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ᱞᱟᱦᱟ ᱥᱮᱱ ᱤᱫᱤ ᱨᱮ ᱢᱚᱸᱰ ᱢᱩᱨᱩᱱ ᱮᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱚᱱᱟ ᱛᱟᱭᱚᱢ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱨᱚᱱᱡᱚᱱ ᱟᱨ ᱵᱷᱟᱨᱩᱪᱟ ᱥᱟᱶᱛᱮ ''[[ᱯᱭᱟᱨ ᱠᱟ ᱯᱚᱧᱪᱚᱱᱟᱢᱟ ᱒]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱕) ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱥᱚᱱᱳ ᱠᱮ ᱴᱤᱴᱩ ᱠᱤ ᱥᱣᱤᱴᱤ]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱘) ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱡᱤ ᱠᱮᱫᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱱᱚᱶᱟ ᱵᱟᱱᱟᱨ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱠᱟ.ᱣᱰᱤ ᱠᱚᱭ ᱦᱟᱛᱟᱣ ᱞᱮᱫᱟ ᱾  ᱚᱱᱟ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱥᱚᱠᱥᱮᱥ ᱛᱟᱭᱚᱢ ᱒᱐᱑᱙ ᱠᱚᱢᱮᱰᱤ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ''[[ᱞᱩᱠᱟ ᱪᱷᱩᱯᱤ]]'' ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱯᱚᱛᱤ ᱯᱚᱛᱱᱤ ᱚᱨ ᱣᱩ (᱒᱐᱑᱙ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ)|ᱯᱚᱛᱤ ᱯᱚᱛᱱᱤ ᱚᱨ ᱣᱩ]]'' ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱧᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟᱭ ᱾

== ᱮᱴᱟᱜ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱠᱚ ==
In addition to acting in films, Aaryan endorses several brands and products, including the sportswear brand [[Hummel International]], the cream [[Emami#Fair And Handsome|Emami Fair And Handsome]] and the clothing brand [[Manyavar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/hummel-signs-bollywood-heartthrob-kartik-aaryan-as-india-brand-ambassador-119021600296_1.html|title=hummel signs bollywood heartthrob, Kartik Aaryan as India Brand Ambassador|date=16 February 2019|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=20 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/advertising/actor-kartik-aaryan-to-endorse-emami-fair-and-handsome/64168970|title=Actor Kartik Aaryan to endorse Emami Fair And Handsome|date=15 May 2018|work=[[The Economic Times]]|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625100146/https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/advertising/actor-kartik-aaryan-to-endorse-emami-fair-and-handsome/64168970|archivedate=25 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/kartik-aaryan-appointed-new-face-ethnic-brand-manyavar/|title=Kartik Aaryan appointed as the new face of ethnic brand Manyavar|date=4 July 2019|work=Bollywood Hungama|access-date=6 July 2019}}</ref> He has also co-hosted the [[19th IIFA Awards|2018 IIFA Awards]] with [[Ayushmann Khurrana]], and the [[Zee Cine Awards|2019 Zee Cine Awards]] with [[Vicky Kaushal]].<ref name="zee"/><ref name="iifa">{{cite news|last=Roy|first=Priyanka|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/the-big-bolly-show-241387|title=The Big Bolly Show|work=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]]|date=1 July 2018|accessdate=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702102355/https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/the-big-bolly-show-241387|archivedate=2 July 2018}}</ref>

In 2016, Aaryan became a member of the All Stars Football Club, which organises football matches for charity.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/kartikaaryanin-all-stars-football-club/article8529466.ece|title=Kartik Aaryan in All Stars Football Club|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2 July 2018|date=28 April 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111164110/https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/kartikaaryanin-all-stars-football-club/article8529466.ece|archivedate=11 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He participated with several other celebrities, including [[Ranbir Kapoor]], for a tournament held in New Delhi the following year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kartik-Aryan-flies-to-New-Delhi-with-Ranbir-Kapoor-for-a-charity-football-match/articleshow/53399448.cms|title=Kartik Aryan flies to New Delhi with Ranbir Kapoor for a charity football match!|date=28 January 2017|work=The Times of India|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517190557/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kartik-Aryan-flies-to-New-Delhi-with-Ranbir-Kapoor-for-a-charity-football-match/articleshow/53399448.cms|archivedate=17 May 2017}}</ref> Aaryan was scheduled to take part in the club's next tournament, held in Singapore in 2018, but had to back out after dislocating his toe during practice.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/this-is-why-kartik-aaryan-will-have-to-ditch-a-charity-event-involving-arjun-and-ranbir-kapoor/articleshow/63817069.cms|title=This is why Kartik Aaryan will have to ditch a charity event involving Arjun and Ranbir Kapoor|date=18 April 2018|work=The Times of India|access-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420122845/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/this-is-why-kartik-aaryan-will-have-to-ditch-a-charity-event-involving-arjun-and-ranbir-kapoor/articleshow/63817069.cms|archivedate=20 April 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Aaryan raised awareness on [[plastic pollution]] during [[World Environment Day]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-world-environment-day-kartik-aaryan-i-stopped-using-plastic-bottles-5-years-ago-2622043|title=World Environment Day: Kartik Aaryan, ‘I stopped using plastic bottles 5 years ago’|date=5 June 2018|work=Daily News and Analysis|access-date=2 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702150613/http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/interview-world-environment-day-kartik-aaryan-i-stopped-using-plastic-bottles-5-years-ago-2622043|archive-date=2 July 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The following year, the [[Election Commission of India]] appointed him to raise awareness on voter participation in his home state of Madhya Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news|author=Roy, Dhaval|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-lok-sabha-election-2019-kartik-aaryan-becomes-the-state-icon-of-madhya-pradesh-2738992|title=Lok Sabha Election 2019: Kartik Aaryan becomes the state icon of Madhya Pradesh|date=13 April 2019|work=Daily News and Analysis|access-date=13 April 2019}}</ref>

Aaryan was placed eighth in ''[[The Times of India]]''{{'}}s listing of the country's most desirable men of 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/vicky-kaushal-is-the-times-most-desirable-man-of-2018/articleshow/69361561.cms|title=Meet India’s most desirable dudes|date=17 May 2019|work=The Times of India|access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref> In 2019, he appeared in ''[[Forbes India]]''{{'s}} [[Forbes Celebrity 100|Celebrity 100]] list, ranking 67th with an estimated annual income of {{INRConvert|103.8|m}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2019-celebrity-100/1819/all |title=2019 Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes India |accessdate=20 December 2018 }}</ref>

